'''
The marks obtained by a student in 3 different subjects are input by the user,
Your program should calculate the average of subjects and and display the grade. 
The student gets a grade as per the following rules:
Average  Grade
90-100  A
80-89   B
70-79   C
60-69	  D
0-59	  F
'''

m1 = float(input("Enter marks of first subject: "))
m2 = float(input("Enter marks of second subject: "))
m3 = float(input("Enter marks of third subject: "))

average = (m1 + m2 + m3) / 3

if average >= 90 and average <= 100:
    grade = 'A'
elif average >= 80:
    grade = 'B'
elif average >= 70:
    grade = 'C'
elif average >= 60:
    grade = 'D'
else:
    grade = 'F'

print("Average Marks:", average)
print("Grade:", grade)

# OUTPUT 
'''
Enter marks of first subject: 85
Enter marks of second subject: 90
Enter marks of third subject: 80
Average Marks: 85.0
Grade: B
'''
